Package com.epam.controller.command

Interface Command

All Known Implementing Classes:
AddTariffCommand, AdminMenuCommand, ChangeLanguageCommand, ChangePasswordCommand, ChangeUserBalanceCommand, ChangeUserStatusCommand, ConnectTariffCommand, DailyWithdrawCommand, DisableTariffCommand, DownloadTariffsCommand, EditTariffCommand, LoginCommand, LogoutCommand, OpenAddTariffCommand, OpenUserRegistrationCommand, RegisterUserCommand, RemoveTariffCommand, RemoveUserCommand, ReplenishCommand, ResetPasswordCommand, ViewAccountCommand, ViewActiveTariffsCommand, ViewProfileCommand, ViewSubscriberAccountCommand, ViewSubscriberProfileCommand, ViewSubscriberTariffsCommand, ViewTariffsCommand
public interface Command
The Command interface is implemented by any class whose instances are intended to represent a command to be executed in the context of a HTTP request and response. The HttpServletRequest, HttpServletResponse method of each implementation class should contain the logic for executing the corresponding command and returning the appropriate string that represents the path of the next JSP page to be displayed to the user.
